hpnicfDlswExt.name: hpnicfDlswExt

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

hpnicfDlswExt.description: The MIB module for management of specific Data Link Switching protocol enhancements. DLSw is described in RFC 1795, RFC 2024 and RFC2166.

hpnicfdeNodeVendorID.name: hpnicfdeNodeVendorID
hpnicfdeNodeVendorID.description: The value identifies the manufacturer's IEEE-assigned Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI) of this DLSw. This information is reported in DLSw Capabilities Exchange.

hpnicfdeNodeIpAddrType.name: hpnicfdeNodeIpAddrType
hpnicfdeNodeIpAddrType.description: The type of ip address: IPv4 or IPv6.

hpnicfdeNodeLocalAddr.name: hpnicfdeNodeLocalAddr
hpnicfdeNodeLocalAddr.description: Local peer ip address. This ip address must have been configured for a port on the router. If no local peer ip address is configured, then this object will be the empty string.

hpnicfdeNodePriority.name: hpnicfdeNodePriority
hpnicfdeNodePriority.description: Peer priority advertised to remote peers in the DLSw Capabilities Exchange. If an end station can reach through more than one peer, the priority of each peer will be considered when a circuit is established. A lower priority indicates that peer will be the preferred choice if there are more than one path to the destination. A value of 65535 indicates the value is meaningless.

hpnicfdeNodeInitPacingWindow.name: hpnicfdeNodeInitPacingWindow
hpnicfdeNodeInitPacingWindow.description: Initial pacing window size. This is the starting size of the pacing window. DLSw uses an adaptive pacing flow control algorithm that automatically adjusts to congestion levels in the network. Pacing windows are used to control how many packets may be sent to a peer before acknowlegement. A value of 65535 indicates the value is meaningless.

hpnicfdeNodeMaxPacingWindow.name: hpnicfdeNodeMaxPacingWindow
hpnicfdeNodeMaxPacingWindow.description: Maximum pacing window size. This is the largest size that the pacing window will grow to. DLSw uses an adaptive pacing flow control algorithm that automatically adjusts to congestion levels in the network. Pacing windows are used to control how many packets may be sent to a peer before acknowlegement.

hpnicfdeNodeKeepAliveInterval.name: hpnicfdeNodeKeepAliveInterval
hpnicfdeNodeKeepAliveInterval.description: Default remote peer keepalive interval in seconds. The keepalive parameter refers to how often DLSw peers send peer keep alives to each other. These periodic messages allow DLSw to keep track of the state of all peers. If set to zero, no keepalives are sent. A value of 65535 indicates the value is meaningless.

hpnicfdeNodePermitDynamic.name: hpnicfdeNodePermitDynamic
hpnicfdeNodePermitDynamic.description: To accept connections from non-configured remote peer when permitDynamic is specified.

hpnicfdeNodeConfigSapList.name: hpnicfdeNodeConfigSapList
hpnicfdeNodeConfigSapList.description: The SAP list indicates which SAPs are allowed. Only SAPs with even numbers are represented, in the form of the most significant bit of the first octet representing the SAP 0, the next most significant bit representing the SAP 2, to the least significant bit of the last octet representing the SAP 254. Data link switching is allowed for those SAPs which have one in its corresponding bit, not allowed otherwise. The whole SAP list has to be changed together. Changing the SAP list affects only new circuit establishments and has no effect on established circuits. This list can be used to restrict specific partners from knowing about all the SAPs used by DLSw on all its interfaces (these are represented in hpnicfdeIfSapList for each interface). For instance, one may want to run NetBIOS with some partners but not others. If a node supports sending run-time capabilities exchange messages, changes to this object should cause that action. When to start the run-time capabilities exchange is implementation-specific. The DEFVAL below indicates support for SAPs 0, 2, 4, 6, 8, A, C and E.

hpnicfdeNodeMaxTransmission.name: hpnicfdeNodeMaxTransmission
hpnicfdeNodeMaxTransmission.description: The maximum retry times for TCP packet. Default value is 5.

hpnicfdeNodeMulticastStatus.name: hpnicfdeNodeMulticastStatus
hpnicfdeNodeMulticastStatus.description: Multicast support status. It is disabled by default.

hpnicfdeNodeMulticastAddress.name: hpnicfdeNodeMulticastAddress
hpnicfdeNodeMulticastAddress.description: Multicast address. Default is 224.0.10.0. When the hpnicfdeNodeMulticastStatus is disabled, the multicast address is reset to 0.0.0.0.

hpnicfdeNodeResetTcpAll.name: hpnicfdeNodeResetTcpAll
hpnicfdeNodeResetTcpAll.description: Reset all TCP circuit switch. Any return value is meaningless.

hpnicfdeNodeStCapTcpNum.name: hpnicfdeNodeStCapTcpNum
hpnicfdeNodeStCapTcpNum.description: Tcp number reported in DLSw Capabilities Exchange.

hpnicfdeNodeTcpQueueMax.name: hpnicfdeNodeTcpQueueMax
hpnicfdeNodeTcpQueueMax.description: The max length of TCP queue.

hpnicfdeTConnConfigTable.name: hpnicfdeTConnConfigTable
hpnicfdeTConnConfigTable.description: This table defines the peer transport connections that will be initiated or accepted by this DLSw. This table augments dlswTConnConfigTable.

hpnicfdeTConnConfigEntry.name: hpnicfdeTConnConfigEntry
hpnicfdeTConnConfigEntry.description: A list of objects that define specific configuration for a DLSw peer transport connection.

hpnicfdeTConnConfigVersion.name: hpnicfdeTConnConfigVersion
hpnicfdeTConnConfigVersion.description: This value identifies which version (first octet) and release (second octet) of the DLSw standard is supported by this partner DLSw. This information is obtained from a DLSw Capabilities Exchange message received from the partner DLSw. A string of zero length is returned before a Capabilities Exchange message is received, or if one is never received. A conceptual row with a hpnicfdeTConnOperState of 'connected' but a zero length partner version indicates that the partner is a non-standard DLSw partner. If an implementation chooses to keep hpnicfdeTConnOperEntrys in the 'disconnected' state, this value should remain unchanged.

hpnicfdeTConnConfigBackup.name: hpnicfdeTConnConfigBackup
hpnicfdeTConnConfigBackup.description: The current remote peer is configured as the backup of another configured remote peer.

hpnicfdeTConnConfigBackupTAddr.name: hpnicfdeTConnConfigBackupTAddr
hpnicfdeTConnConfigBackupTAddr.description: It is the ip address of a configured remote peer of which the current remote peer is configrued as backup.

hpnicfdeTConnOperTable.name: hpnicfdeTConnOperTable
hpnicfdeTConnOperTable.description: A list of peer transport connections. Each connected peer will create a conceptual row in the table. When the peer disconnects, the row will be deleted from the table. This table augments dlswTConnOperTable.

hpnicfdeTConnOperEntry.name: hpnicfdeTConnOperEntry
hpnicfdeTConnOperEntry.description: A list of objects that contain spefific operational information for a DLSw peer transport connection.

hpnicfdeTConnOperPeerType.name: hpnicfdeTConnOperPeerType
hpnicfdeTConnOperPeerType.description: The current remote peer is configured when the value is 'configured'.

hpnicfdeTConnOperVendorID.name: hpnicfdeTConnOperVendorID
hpnicfdeTConnOperVendorID.description: The value identifies the manufacturer's IEEE-assigned Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI) of remote peer.

hpnicfdeTConnOperVersionString.name: hpnicfdeTConnOperVersionString
hpnicfdeTConnOperVersionString.description: Version information of remote peer. The length up to 512 bytes.

hpnicfdeTConnOperUpTime.name: hpnicfdeTConnOperUpTime
hpnicfdeTConnOperUpTime.description: The amount of time (in seconds) since this transport connection last entered the 'connected' state.

hpnicfdeTConnOperMulticastAddress.name: hpnicfdeTConnOperMulticastAddress
hpnicfdeTConnOperMulticastAddress.description: When remote peer supports DLSw2.0, this node identifies its multicast address.

hpnicfdeTConnOperStCapTcpNumber.name: hpnicfdeTConnOperStCapTcpNumber
hpnicfdeTConnOperStCapTcpNumber.description: Number of tcp supported when capabilities exchanging.

hpnicfdeTConnOperRecvPkts.name: hpnicfdeTConnOperRecvPkts
hpnicfdeTConnOperRecvPkts.description: The number of Switch-to-Switch Protocol (SSP) messages received on this tcp transport connection.

hpnicfdeTConnOperSendPkts.name: hpnicfdeTConnOperSendPkts
hpnicfdeTConnOperSendPkts.description: The number of SSP messages sent on this tcp transport connection.

hpnicfdeTConnOperDropPkts.name: hpnicfdeTConnOperDropPkts
hpnicfdeTConnOperDropPkts.description: The number of SSP messages dropped on this tcp transport connection.

hpnicfdeTConnTcpConfigTable.name: hpnicfdeTConnTcpConfigTable
hpnicfdeTConnTcpConfigTable.description: This table defines the TCP transport connections that will be either initiated by or accepted by this DSLw. It augments the entries in dlswTConnConfigTable whose domain is dlswTCPDomain. In other words for each conceptual row in the dlswTConnConfigTable, if the dlswTConnConfigTDomain is dlswTCPDomain, that conceptual row will be augmented by this table. dlswTCPDomain, dlswTConnConfigTable, and dlswTConnConfigTDomain are all imported from DLSW-MIB (RFC 2024). This table augments dlswTConnTcpConfigTable.

hpnicfdeTConnTcpConfigEntry.name: hpnicfdeTConnTcpConfigEntry
hpnicfdeTConnTcpConfigEntry.description: A list of objects that define specific configuration for a DLSw peer transport connection within the dlswTCPDomain. dlswTCPDomain is imported from DLSW-MIB (RFC 2024).

hpnicfdeTConnTcpConfigQueueMax.name: hpnicfdeTConnTcpConfigQueueMax
hpnicfdeTConnTcpConfigQueueMax.description: Maximum output TCP queue size for this remote peer. For DLSw over TCP encapsulation, packets may be queued due to congestion of the TCP network. This variable is used to set the output queue maximum of the underlying TCP connection for the peer represented by the conceptual row.

hpnicfdeBridgeTable.name: hpnicfdeBridgeTable
hpnicfdeBridgeTable.description: A list of bridge group which is serving for DLSw.

hpnicfdeBridgeNumIndex.name: hpnicfdeBridgeNumIndex
hpnicfdeBridgeNumIndex.description: This value identifies the bridge number.

hpnicfdeBridgeIfTable.name: hpnicfdeBridgeIfTable
hpnicfdeBridgeIfTable.description: The list of interface on which DLSw is active.

hpnicfdeBridgeIfEntry.name: hpnicfdeBridgeIfEntry
hpnicfdeBridgeIfEntry.description: The list of bridge interface information.

hpnicfdeBridgeIfBrgGrp.name: hpnicfdeBridgeIfBrgGrp
hpnicfdeBridgeIfBrgGrp.description: This value identifies the bridge number attached to the interface.

hpnicfdeQllcTable.name: hpnicfdeQllcTable
hpnicfdeQllcTable.description: The table defines attributes related for those QLLC that participate in data link switching.

hpnicfdeQllcEntry.name: hpnicfdeQllcEntry
hpnicfdeQllcEntry.description: The ifIndex belongs to the interface which link protocol is x.25.

hpnicfQllcLocalMac.name: hpnicfQllcLocalMac
hpnicfQllcLocalMac.description: The virtual MAC address used to represent the QLLC-attached link station to the rest of the DLSw network.

hpnicfQllcLocalSap.name: hpnicfQllcLocalSap
hpnicfQllcLocalSap.description: The SAP used to represent this link station.

hpnicfQllcRemoteMac.name: hpnicfQllcRemoteMac
hpnicfQllcRemoteMac.description: The MAC address to which DLSw should attempt to connect this link station. If this information is not available, a length of zero for this object should be returned.

hpnicfQllcRemoteSap.name: hpnicfQllcRemoteSap
hpnicfQllcRemoteSap.description: The SAP of the remote station to which this link station should be connected. If this information is not available, a length of zero for this object should be returned.

hpnicfdeSdlcPortTable.name: hpnicfdeSdlcPortTable
hpnicfdeSdlcPortTable.description: The table defines parameters for the interfaces whose link protocol is SDLC.

hpnicfdeSdlcPortMaxTransmission.name: hpnicfdeSdlcPortMaxTransmission
hpnicfdeSdlcPortMaxTransmission.description: Number of times to retry an operation.

hpnicfdeSdlcPortTimerACK.name: hpnicfdeSdlcPortTimerACK
hpnicfdeSdlcPortTimerACK.description: Time to wait for a reply to a frame.

hpnicfdeSdlcPortTimerLifeTime.name: hpnicfdeSdlcPortTimerLifeTime
hpnicfdeSdlcPortTimerLifeTime.description: Time to wait for a reply used by secondary station.

hpnicfdeSdlcPortTimerPollPause.name: hpnicfdeSdlcPortTimerPollPause
hpnicfdeSdlcPortTimerPollPause.description: Time between polls for each secondary SDLC station.

hpnicfdeLlc2PortTable.name: hpnicfdeLlc2PortTable
hpnicfdeLlc2PortTable.description: This table defines parameters for the Ethernet interface.

hpnicfdeLlc2PortMaxAck.name: hpnicfdeLlc2PortMaxAck
hpnicfdeLlc2PortMaxAck.description: Maximum of I-frames received before ACK.

hpnicfdeLlc2PortReceiveWindow.name: hpnicfdeLlc2PortReceiveWindow
hpnicfdeLlc2PortReceiveWindow.description: Maximum number of I-frames to send before received ACK.

hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerAck.name: hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerAck
hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerAck.description: Waiting for ACK time after sending an I-frame.

hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerAckDelay.name: hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerAckDelay
hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerAckDelay.description: Maximum time allows I-frames incoming without replay ACK.

hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerBusy.name: hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerBusy
hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerBusy.description: Waiting time while other LLC2 station is in busy state.

hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerPoll.name: hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerPoll
hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerPoll.description: Waiting time after a P frame is sent.

hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerReject.name: hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerReject
hpnicfdeLlc2PortTimerReject.description: Waiting time after a REJ frame is sent.

hpnicfdeRchCacheNextIndex.name: hpnicfdeRchCacheNextIndex
hpnicfdeRchCacheNextIndex.description: The next value of hpnicfdeRchCacheIndex to be assigned by the agent. A retrieval of this object atomically reserves the returned value for use by the manager to create a row in hpnicfdeRchCacheTable. This makes it possible for the agent to control the index space of the MAC address cache, yet allows the manager to administratively create new rows.

hpnicfdeRchCacheStatus.name: hpnicfdeRchCacheStatus
hpnicfdeRchCacheStatus.description: Current status of reachable cache entry.

hpnicfdeRchCacheRemainTime.name: hpnicfdeRchCacheRemainTime
hpnicfdeRchCacheRemainTime.description: Remain time of reachable cache entry.

hpnicfdeRchCacheMac.name: hpnicfdeRchCacheMac
hpnicfdeRchCacheMac.description: MAC address of reachable cache entry.

hpnicfdeRchCacheRemoteIp.name: hpnicfdeRchCacheRemoteIp
hpnicfdeRchCacheRemoteIp.description: Remote peer ip address of reachable cache entry.

hpnicfdeEBMacMapNextIndex.name: hpnicfdeEBMacMapNextIndex
hpnicfdeEBMacMapNextIndex.description: The next value of hpnicfdeEBMacMapIndex to be assigned by the agent. A retrieval of this object atomically reserves the returned value for use by the manager to create a row in hpnicfdeEBMacMapTable. This makes it possible for the agent to control the index space of the MAC mapping tables, yet allows the manager to administratively create new rows.

hpnicfdeEBIfTable.name: hpnicfdeEBIfTable
hpnicfdeEBIfTable.description: Information of interface which works for DLSw Ethernet redundancy.

hpnicfdeEBIfEntry.name: hpnicfdeEBIfEntry
hpnicfdeEBIfEntry.description: Parameters defined for DLSw Ethernet redundancy interface.

hpnicfdeEBMulticastMac.name: hpnicfdeEBMulticastMac
hpnicfdeEBMulticastMac.description: Multicast MAC address configured for the Ethernet redundancy of dlsw module. When Ethernet redundancy is inactive, its value is '000000000000'H. To active Ethernet redundancy, give it a valid multicast MAC address.

hpnicfdeEBPriority.name: hpnicfdeEBPriority
hpnicfdeEBPriority.description: Priority configured for the Ethernet redundancy of DLSw module.

hpnicfdeEBtimer.name: hpnicfdeEBtimer
hpnicfdeEBtimer.description: Timer for the Ethernet redundancy of DLSw module.

hpnicfdeEBMacMapIndex.name: hpnicfdeEBMacMapIndex
hpnicfdeEBMacMapIndex.description: Index of MAC address mapping entry.

hpnicfdeEBMacMapLocalMac.name: hpnicfdeEBMacMapLocalMac
hpnicfdeEBMacMapLocalMac.description: Local MAC address in MAC address mapping. When creating a new conceptual row, hpnicfdeEBMacMapLocalMac and hpnicfdeEBMacMapRemoteMac should be set simultaneously.

hpnicfdeEBMacMapRemoteMac.name: hpnicfdeEBMacMapRemoteMac
hpnicfdeEBMacMapRemoteMac.description: Remote MAC address of MAC address mapping. When creating a new conceptual row, hpnicfdeEBMacMapLocalMac and hpnicfdeEBMacMapRemoteMac should be set simultaneously.

hpnicfdeEBMacMapRowStatus.name: hpnicfdeEBMacMapRowStatus
hpnicfdeEBMacMapRowStatus.description: Status of MAC address mapping entry.
